meanings.definition: Not belonging to or characteristic of the elite.
meanings.sent1: The nonelite students were excited to participate in the school play.
meanings.sent2: She preferred the nonelite brand of clothing over the expensive designer labels.
meanings.sent3: The nonelite squirrel tried to join the elite squirrel club but was denied due to its humble acorn collection.
meanings.sent4: In the forest, the nonelite trees stood tall and proud, not overshadowed by the elite towering oaks.
meanings.sent5: The nonelite team fought bravely against the elite champions, showing great determination.

meanings.definition: A person or group not belonging to the elite.
meanings.sent1: The nonelite in the community worked hard to support each other.
meanings.sent2: She felt a sense of belonging among the nonelite of the town.
meanings.sent3: The nonelite club members organized a fun picnic to celebrate their uniqueness.
meanings.sent4: He saw himself as a lone wolf among the nonelite, navigating his own path.
meanings.sent5: The nonelite group shared stories of their struggles and triumphs, forming a strong bond.
